<br>
Instead of removing that line, I simply went into a copy of the default castingwindow.xml file and made the size of all pieces and the background 0 X by 0 Y, so the window is still included, but invisible.<br>
<br>
I guess the reason I made this mod was so that I had all of the information I wanted as quickly as possible without looking all over my screen for it.  I spend alot of time looking at my casting bar and the health status of my target and I figured i might as well make it look interesting.  For healers the globe that changes colors from green to yellow to orange to pulsating red indicates when a certain type of healing spell is needed at a mere glance, and the % numeric label is centrally located to give a precise value.<br>
<br>
Ahh well, maybe I will make a mod that is less artistic, but still uses the animated gauges so it is kinda cool, hehe   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I do think this mod is addictive though, although it certainly is an aquired taste for those used to plain numbers and bars.<br>
<br>
